    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 6.7,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.7,
      "end": 14.86,
      "text": "information and to find out how to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org. Recording by Marion",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 14.86,
      "end": 23.24,
      "text": "Brown, Toronto, Canada. ASOP's Fables. The Lion and the Bull. Chapter 17.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 24.5,
      "end": 31.4,
      "text": "A lion saw a fine fat bull pasturing among a herd of cattle and cast about for some means",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 31.4,
      "end": 37.84,
      "text": "of getting him into his clutches. So he sent him words that he was sacrificing a sheep and",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 37.84,
      "end": 43.26,
      "text": "asked if he would do him the honour of dining with him. The bull accepted the invitation.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 44.32,
      "end": 50.5,
      "text": "But, on arriving at the lion's den, he saw a great array of saucepans and spits, but",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 50.5,
      "end": 57.0,
      "text": "no sign of a sheep. So he turned on his heel and walked quietly away. The lion called",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 57.0,
      "end": 63.28,
      "text": "after him in an injured tone to ask the reason, and the bull turned round and said, I have",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 63.28,
      "end": 69.42,
      "text": "reason enough. When I saw all your preparations, it struck me at once that the victim was to",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 69.42,
      "end": 75.96,
      "text": "be a bull and not a sheep. The net is spread in vain in sight of the bird.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 75.96,
      "end": 80.6,
      "text": "End of ASOP's Fable. The Lion and the Bull.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
